the specifications was rewarded handsomely for their efforts.  Quasqueton Fyrestrike was confident he was one of those people and had spent the past few weeks gathering the materials he needed, preparing the parts of the armor short of formally forging the pieces as time and equipment permitted.  Obsessively lost in his work, he was not paying any attention to the bard, then he jabbed his hand with his leather puncher and cursed profusely.  Autumn snickered.<br><br>  &quot;The length of time it takes me to complete this padding impacts how long we stay here.  Hopefully this will be enough.  But if I ruin a pelt I'll need to replace it.&quot;  The silver haired wizard pointed to the silvery white furs stacked near a plethora of tailoring and leatherworking tools scattered around.  &quot;So we can't leave yet.&quot;<br><br>  &quot;Alright, alright.&quot;  Autumn sighed and looked around.  She saw a small outline in the distance.  Even after donning the mask to take the appearance of a dark elf with their superior ultravision, she couldn't quite make out the form but it looked like another velium hound on the prowl.  She readied her sword, once more Quasqueton was engrossed in his work and didn't seem to notice her actions.  Singing the song of Selo's, Autumn broke into a run and headed off in that direction.  After following a somewhat circular path, Autumn realized the hound was heading deliberately for Quasqueton, not in the stalker's pace though.  Slowing down, she figured it was likely someone intent on requesting that the wizard transport them somewhere out of this barren wasteland.<br><br>Millikin saw the wizard some distance away and trotted closer.  She quickly noticed that he was leatherworking and waited silently for several moments.  Feeling he was being watched, Quasqueton looked up to see a dire wolf staring at him.  He quickly jumped to his feet and whispered an incantation.  Motes of flame erupted from his fingertips, when he realized the wolf had not attacked and he closed his hand into a fist to quickly dissipate the fiery energy he was gathering in anticipation of an attack.  He studied it closer.  Druids that were capable of surviving out in the Western Wastes usually opted to travel in the guise of a small jet black wolf.  This one was larger and brown.  <br><br>  &quot;May I help you, Ranger?&quot;  Quasqueton queried after a moment.<br><br>  &quot;I have a message for you.  From...&quot;  Millikin paused, still considering the irony.  &quot;your wife.&quot;<br><br>  &quot;Shio?  What did she possibly say to persuade you to track me all the way out here?&quot;<br><br>  &quot;She is a kinsman of mine.&quot;  Millikin mentally willed the transformation back into her elven form and reached into her backpack searching for the letter.  &quot;And for most intents and purposes, now so are you.&quot;  She handed him Shiobahn's note as Autumn came up from behind her, still wearing her dark elven disguise.<br><br>  &quot;A family reunion?&quot;  Autumn laughed.  Millikin turned around<br>  <br>  &quot;You're still wearing that damned dark elf disguise?&quot;  <br><br>  &quot;Oh hush up, Ranger.  You'd be surprised at how well I can see when using it.&quot;  Autumn quipped.<br><br>  &quot;Why hadn't she mentioned it before?&quot;  Quas took the letter and opened it to read.<br><br>  &quot;I found out Shiobahn was recently married.  The entire prospect is rather frightening to dwell on.&quot;  Millikin replied.<br><br>  &quot;Well, it was somewhat impromptu.&quot;  Quasqueton looked up from the letter.  &quot;Don't worry.  Your cousin is in good hands and capable of fending for herself fairly well.&quot;<br><br>  &quot;I was more concerned about the safety of the general population of Norrath.&quot;  Autumn snickered softly at Millikin's comment.<br><br>  &quot;And just what is THAT supposed to mean?&quot;  Quasqueton huffed.  Millikin glanced northwards, in the direction of the Temple of Veeshan, her thoughts distracted.  &quot;Can I send you somewhere, &quot;cousin&quot;?  He asked, his tone laced with a touch of sarcasm.  Millikin looked at him after a moment.<br><br>  &quot;Just the thought of two fire crazy wizards running loose and working in concert is...&quot;<br><br>  &quot;Frightening.&quot;  Autumn stated deadpan.<br><br>  &quot;... disconcerting.&quot;  Millikin tacked on.  Grinning slightly to Autumn.<br><br>  &quot;I'll be sure to torch a tree or two just for you.&quot;  Quasqueton gazed poignantly at Millikin, his eyes glinted with a trace of humor.<br><br>  &quot;I know of a very large one you can't possibly miss.&quot;  The ranger replied dryly.  &quot;It's called the Earthmelder.&quot;<br><br>  &quot;Hrmph.&quot;  Quasqueton sniffed, knowing exactly the &quot;tree&quot; that the ranger was referring to.  <br><br>  &quot;Actually, I don't know if you're familiar with her or not, nor if you keep up with practitioners of enchantment but do you know the Luhtmauyar Valdayana D`Varr?  I've something for her.&quot;<br><br>Quasqueton tucked the letter away into a pocket and a sudden rumbling was heard in the distance, indicative that a storm was approaching.<br><br>  &quot;D`Varr?  The name's familiar but I'm fairly sure I haven't met her formally.  Sorry.&quot;  He replied.<br><br>  &quot;Its almost as if she's fallen from the face of Norrath.&quot;  Millikin shook her head.  Snow began to fall at a steady pace and even gave Millikin pause.  Why didn't the animals seek cover beforehand?<br><br>  &quot;It seems almost unnatural.&quot;  She remarked mostly to herself.<br><br>  &quot;If you've a hunch of where she is, I can send you there.  Or close by.&quot;  Quasqueton offered, presuming that Millikin was speaking of the one whom she was searching for. <br><br>  &quot;If you could, the Nexus of Luclin please.  It will be easier to start from there.&quot;<br><br>  &quot;I really hate this place.&quot;  Autumn mumbled.  Quasqueton Fyrestrike gripped his staff and began another incantation, summoning energies to tear through the borders of time and space.  He calmly watched as they gathered around the ranger.  <br><br>  &quot;To the Great Divide, Autumn?&quot;  He paused.  For a brief second the eldritch beams that gathered around the ranger had disjoined but they quickly reformed and then she was gone.<br><br>~~~~~<br><br>Luhtmauyar - Elvish for Enchanter.  Derived from the Grey Company's Elvish dictionary specifically in reference to their role in EQ, as opposed to simply meaning &quot;one who enchants&quot;<br>Go to www.grey-company.org for more specifics.<br><br><br>Autumnwyld Crescendo is the sole property of her creator and used only for roleplaying purposes with prior consent.  Do not duplicate.<br><br>Quasqueton Fyrestrike is the sole property of his creator and used only for role playing purposes with prior consent.  Do not duplicate.<br><br>Millikin Erreene is the sole property of her creator for role playing purposes with prior consent.  Do not duplicate.<br><br> <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub51.ezboard.com/flormani79848frm9.showPrevMessage?topicID=15.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub51.ezboard.com/flormani79848frm9.showNextMessage?topicID=15.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a self href=http://pub51.ezboard.com/flormani79848frm9.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=15.topic&index=6><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/softsky/addReply.gif border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub51.ezboard.com/flormani79848frm9.emailToFriend?topicID=15.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub51.ezboard.com/flormani79